## Hard invariants

- GC-only and ownership-aware lowering preserve the same source semantics.
- Borrow validation reads HIR and writes side tables. It does not rewrite HIR or perform backend lowering.
- No compiler or backend path may rely on unchecked aliasing or undefined behaviour to make the ownership model work.
